and find a pickup group. Maybe it is the masochist in me but there is nothing like being told how to play my character by someone that does not have a clue. In my pickup group the monk begins to tell me…<br>
<br>
“Just play the SOW song. I like to run fast.” He did not care that I could lull a camp, debuff a mob, buff the entire group, and deal a bit of damage. He just wanted to run fast, and we were not even going anywhere. That is when I realized, I’m not a bard, I’m a jukebox. Put in a PP and choose a song. Someday I will level up to being a bar band, watching drunken brawlers from the stage while they fight amongst themselves and shout up request for my next song.<br>
<br>
Rabid Littletree, and sometimes known as Music, the jukebox. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/udelane01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delane01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#993300>(3/16/01 7:30:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ok bards, I think I have it figured out.</span><hr size=1> Of all the classes in EQ...I think the bard is told most by others how they should play.<br>
<br>
A bard pulling..thats just stupid..thats what a tank is for..besides I need mana song!<br>
<br>
A bard doing dmg shield..thats just stupid..I don't care if its a 27pt dmg shield that stacks!<br>
<br>
A bard acting as an enchanter...that is way too dangerous...no way..either get a chanter or I will not come.<br>
<br>
Anyway...  Next most abused classes is probably Shaman.  I need this buff and this buff and this buff...  Then they get mad when the shaman casts the group buff rather than the indivdial buff...even though time and time again it has been shown stats dont mean a whole lot.<br>
<br>
Anyway...<br>
<br>
/rant off<br>
<br>
